the working class goes to heaven ( italian : la classe operaia va in paradiso ) is a 1971 political drama film directed by elio petri .   it depicts a factory worker 's realisation of his own condition as a simple " tool " in the process of production and , implicitly , his struggle with the trade unions .   the film competed at the 1972 cannes film festival , where it tied for the grand prix international du festival , the highest honour .   in italy , it also won the david di donatello for best film .